ribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."],"variants":[{"name":"Marsha","meanings":["Phonetic spelling of   Marcia  , associated particularly with the American film star  Marsha Hunt  (  b. 1917 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":56,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705202,"age":65,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705205,"age":76,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705207,"age":92,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705208,"age":94,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Marcia Shay was born from about 1493 to 1498, in England as the daughter of Hugh Shaa and Margret Harsnep. She married Richard Kinne  Keeny  Kinney in 1515, in London, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 2 daughters."},"et":{"from about 1493 to 1498–":"umbes 1493 kuni 1498–Surnud","1493–1514":"1493–1514","1493–Female":"1493–Surnud","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1619":"1521–1619","1525–Male":"1525–Surnud","1527–Male":"1527–Surnud","1529–Female":"1529–Surnud","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","–1567":"–1567","1550":"1550","1493":"1493","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1514":"1514","1567":"1567","1600":"1600","from about 1493 to 1498":"umbes 1493 kuni 1498","1521":"1521","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1619":"1619","1529":"1529","1527":"1527","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","21 August 1492":"21. august 1492","England":"England","Croston,Lancashire,England":"Croston, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England":"London, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"from about 1493 to 1498–":"vuodesta noin 1493 vuoteen 1498–Kuollut","1493–1514":"1493–1514","1493–Female":"1493–Kuollut","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1619":"1521–1619","1525–Male":"1525–Kuollut","1527–Male